law.text:
Subject to the hearing provisions of § 10-404 of this subtitle, the Comptroller may deny registration to an applicant, reprimand a registrant, or suspend or revoke the registration of a petroleum transporter if the applicant or registrant:
fraudulently or deceptively obtains or attempts to obtain the registration for the applicant or registrant or for another person;
fraudulently or deceptively uses the registration;
fails to submit a report required under § 10-410 of this subtitle;
submits false information in a report required under § 10-410 of this subtitle; or
violates this subtitle.
